metatags.og:description:
Entrepreneur, Author & Investor · I'm an entrepreneur, author, public speaker, investor, Broadway co-producer, and lover of adventure travel.

Professionally, I most recently spent twelve years focused on building a more human Future of Work, co-founding The Muse in 2011 and leading the business as CEO from 2011-2023. During that time The Muse grew from 0 to 70+ million annual users, pioneered the concept of values-based job search and was named one of Fast Company's 50 Most Innovative Companies in the World. 

Personally, I'm a wildly passionate traveler -- 72 countries and counting -- proud NYC resident, and avid lover of snacks.

I'm also an active advisor, angel investor (88% in female founded companies), and an Operating Partner with XFactor Ventures, designed to be the “first check” in female founded startups. She has spoken at MIT and Harvard, appeared on The TODAY Show and CNN, and contributes on career and entrepreneurship topics to the Wall Street Journal and Harvard Business Review.
